VVisakha Music and Dance Academy featured a vocal recital at its auditorium Kalabharathi last Saturday. Director and Principal of the Sri Shanmukhananda Bharateeya Sangeetha Mahavidyalay affiliated to Mumbai University, . Radha Namboodri, was the vocalist.Radha, who is a Sangeetha vidwan from the Central College of Carnatic Music at Chennai in 1968, seemed to be a resplendent revelation of the ideal musician evolved in her. It was a result of soulful sadhana under the sagacious tutelage and supervision of Semmangudi Srinivasa Iyer and his prime disciple T.M. Thyagarajan, while she was a paid scholar of Government of India after 1968. No wonder she adopted a leisurely and reposeful tempo all along and unblemished punctuation, pronunciation along with pliable intoning of each and every note and syllable with commensurable intensity. Thus she could surface the multifarious hues of emotions embedded in the musical and lyrical phraseology of the variety of compositions she rendered.Her repertoire mainly hadDevadeva(Mayamalavagoula) with swaram, elaboration ofMamava Meenakshi(Varali),Dvaithamu Sukhama(Reethigoula) and most eruditely rendered ragam, tanam and pallavi in Sankarabharanam in Aditaalam.Senior violin lecturer of MR Govt. College, Ch. Sanyasi Rao and noteworthy mridanga vidwan G. Venkata Rao proved to be her peers both in their following and turns
